LTA_REPEATED_CALLS_DESC: Reports when identical calls are made within a small window of time.
LTA_REPEATED_CALLS_VIOLATION: Repeated call found {0} other times in calls to endpoint.
LTA_BATCH_CALLS_DESC: Detects when a series of batch API calls are made close together that can potentially be combined to reduce the overall number of calls to the endpoint.
LTA_BATCH_CALLS_DATA_ALLOWED: Allowed Time Between Calls in ms
LTA_BATCH_CALLS_VIOLATION: A set of {0} Batch Calls was found within a time window of ({1}ms) to endpoint. Total XUID count ({2}). Consider combining into one call.
LTA_BURST_CALLS_DESC: Analyzes the calls frequency and detects periods of increased calls for investigation.
LTA_BURST_CALLS_VIOLATION: Burst increase of {0} calls to endpoint found.
LTA_FREQ_CALLS_DESC: Analyzes the frequency of calls over the length of the capture and reports the number of times that the title exceeded the expected limits.
LTA_FREQ_CALLS_VIOLATION_EXCEEDED: Exceeding rate limits for '{0}' required for title certification( limit of {1} calls with {2} calls in {3} seconds).  Failure to adhere to the specified limits may block a title from release, and in-production issues with released titles may result in service suspension up to and including title removal.
LTA_FREQ_CALLS_VIOLATION_SUSTAINED: Call frequency above the sustained call limit for '{0}' (limit of {1} exceeded with {2} calls in {3} seconds).
LTA_FREQ_CALLS_VIOLATION_BURST: Call frequency above the burst call limit for '{0}' (limit of {1} exceeded with {2} calls in {3} seconds).
LTA_FREQ_CALLS_VIOLATION_SHORT: Average time of {0}ms between calls is too short
LTA_FREQ_CALLS_VIOLATION_LONG: Calls are taking longer than expected to return {0}ms
LTA_FREQ_CALLS_VIOLATION_MAX: The maximum call time for calls is greater than allowed {0}ms
LTA_POLL_CALLS_DESC: Finds sequences of calls that appear to be polling of a service.
LTA_POLL_CALLS_VIOLATION: Polling detected in a sequence of {0} calls at a rate of approximately {1} min:sec
LTA_SMALL_CALLS_DESC: Detects uses of batch APIs with a small number of users.
LTA_SMALL_CALLS_VIOLATION: Batch call detected for endpoint for a small sized set of {0} XUIDs.
LTA_THROTTLE_CALLS_DESC: Reports the number of throttled calls per endpoint. Multiple throttled call indicates the title is not properly handling a 429 response. See results.log for call limits.
LTA_THROTTLE_CALLS_VIOLATION_MULTI: Sequence of throttled calls detected on endpoint.
